1.5 The purpose of the CommerceBlock Network project is to bring a combination of
trust minimized trade, decentralised contract execution, on-chain derivatives and
asset-backed token issuance to public blockchains using a new distributed ledger-
2
based platform Network and for which the Company provides a number of
incentivisation mechanisms. Further information is available in the White Paper.
1.6 Once developed and built the Network is intended to focus on creating a decentralised
finance network.
1.7 The Network project is being made possible by contributions from the community in
the form of purchase of Tokens that will enable Network development and
development and support of the associated eco-system. The Token Sale is therefore
intended to give Contributors the ability to support and transact on the Network.
1.8 Tokens will be an integral part of the Network as a means to support and intermediate
services between users.
1.9 The Tokens are intended to fulfil the following functions:
(a) Network access;
(b) API licences;
(c) service usage; &
(d) rewards.
1.10 The Contributions from the Token Sale will be distributed as follows:
(a) Software development: 50%
(b) Operations: 20%
(c) Marketing: 15%
(d) Open-source software development: 15%
1.11 The Tokens will be distributed as specified in the Website: Token value will likely

4. TOKEN SALE
4.1 In consideration of payment of the Contributions, the Company will, or will ensure
that the Token Issuing Entity will, allocate the Contributor the number of Tokens
specified according to the White Paper to be paid into Your Wallet from Our Wallet
after the closing of the Token Sale.
4.2 Commencement and Duration. The Company will conduct a public sale of Tokens
(i.e. the Token Sale), which will begin at 4pm UTC on 28 November 2017 (the
Launch Date) and end at 4pm UTC on 19 December 2017 or when 400,000,000
Tokens have been sold, whichever is earlier (although we may extend the deadline for
additional time if necessary to address any unforeseen technical difficulties and
provided that we notify you of the same) (Availability Period).
4.3 Tokens shall be available during the Availability Period, after which no more tokens
will be created.
4.4 A total of 1 Billion Tokens shall be issued in respect of both the Token Pre-Sale and
the Token Sale, which shall be subject to a “hard-cap” of USD 25 Million. The
Company reserves the right to increase the percentage of Tokens it sells or has sold,
to private Contributors via the Token Pre-Sale.
4.5 The Tokens shall be distributed in the following proportions:
6
● Contributors: a maximum of 40% of Total Tokens;
● Enterprise Partner Reserve: 30% - will be allocated to reward early
adopters and provide liquidity to the market if required.
● Company Team: 30% - will be allocated as rewards for our advisors and
team. Of this, a maximum of 10% will be released one month following
closure of the Token Sale (advisors and team) and the following 90% will be
released in annual tranches of 4% starting a year after the closure of the
Token Sale.
Contribution Failure
4.6 In the event that Contributions of less than $1,500,000 are received this shall result in
withdrawal of the Token Sale (Contribution Failure) and the Token Sale shall be
abandoned, no Tokens shall be issued and all Contributions shall be returned to you
in full and final settlement of any obligations related to the Token Sale and your
intention to acquire Tokens. These Terms shall terminate immediately upon return of
your Contribution to Your Wallet.
Price Must Be Received in Full Within 72 Hours
4.7 On your application to make a Contribution, we shall issue you with individual
payment instructions.
4.8 If we have not received the payment of the full Price to Our Wallet within:
(a) 1 hour of the time that you receive the payment instructions, the amount of
Tokens that you receive shall be made in accordance with the applicable
Exchange Rate at the time your Contribution is deemed to have been
received; or
(b) 72 hours of the time that you receive the payment instructions, we reserve
the right to void your purchase request and refuse to accept your purchase of
Tokens. For the avoidance of doubt, the Price will be deemed to be paid in
full once we have received: six BTC or twelve ETH network confirmations
of the transaction. We reserve the right, in our sole discretion, to modify any
of the timelines described herein to account for network congestion or other
technical challenges.
4.9 You must pay the Price by sending the correct quantity of ETH or BTC (as
applicable) to the unique address displayed to you via the sale portal. Your purchase
is not guaranteed until we receive the entire amount of the Price.
Delivery of Tokens
4.10 We will deliver the quantity of Tokens you purchase by the later of:
● three (3) weeks after the Availability Period (although we may extend the
delivery deadline for up to two (2) additional weeks if necessary to address any
unforeseen technical difficulties), or
● one (1) week after you have provided a complete and accurate details of Your
Wallet. For the avoidance of doubt, any such extension shall not affect the
7
parties’ obligations to make and take delivery, respectively, of Tokens
purchased.
Possible Migration of Tokens.
4.11 Tokens are being created as ERC-20 tokens on the Ethereum protocol. We reserve
the right to migrate the ERC-20 based Tokens (Pre-existing Tokens) to another
protocol and to generate replacement Tokens on the new protocol (Replacement
Tokens) in the future, should we determine, in our sole discretion, that doing so is
necessary or useful to the operation of the Network.
4.12 Should we decide to migrate the Tokens, we may no longer provide support for the
Pre-existing Tokens relating to the Network except with respect to the migration
process. Although we do not at this time anticipate that it will require any Pre-
existing Tokenholders to convert their Pre-existing Tokens to Replacement Tokens,
we anticipate there will be significant incentives for Pre-existing Tokenholders to do
so, since the practical utility of Pre-existing Tokens will likely diminish rapidly once
the Replacement Tokens are created and in use by a significant portion of Network
participants. Accordingly, you acknowledge and agree that in order for you to
continue to participate in the Network or obtain utility from the Tokens you may need
to convert the Tokens you purchase during the Sale to Replacement Tokens in the
future.
4.13 Should we decide to migrate the Tokens, we will notify you via the email address you
provided us with. You are solely responsible for updating us should your contact
information change.
4.14 You understand and acknowledge that, as the Tokens may be smart-contract based,
their functionality is dependant on the ETH blockchain Smart Contract System
(SCS): no other document or communication may modify or add any additional
obligations or covenants for the Token Issuing Entity beyond those outlined in these
Terms. In the event of any conflict between the SCS and these Terms, these Terms

Issuance of Tokens under the SCS
5.18 Issuance of the respective entries of the Public Key (PUK) of Tokenholders are made
by the Smart Contract System on the Blockchain according to the allocation
information in the SCS.
5.19 The creation and allocation of Tokens by the SCS are initiated by the User sending
ETH/BTC to the SCS, which triggers a smart contract operation. The SCS creates and
allocates the corresponding Tokens to the User’s wallet address (i.e. from where the
ETH/BTC was sent from). Contributors shall therefore ensure that they make a
Contribution using an ETH/BTC address with which the SCS can operate (e.g. not an
address of a cryptocurrency exchange service provider).

experimental. Participation in the proposed Token Sale and Network project therefore

businesses will still be in an early development stage and unproven, and there is an

cryptocurrency contributions into one or more fiat and/or alternative cryptocurrencies
